<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-2376] Escape character in JPQL with parameter substitution generates incorrect SQL</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-2376</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Escape character in JPQL/SQL with parameter substitution generates incorrect SQL. E.g.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;SELECT &apos;TRUE&apos; AS VAL FROM DUAL WHERE &apos;&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;&apos; = ?&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;SELECT * FROM ( SELECT FOLDER_ID, SYS_CONNECT_BY_PATH(NAME,&apos;&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;&apos;) AS PATH FROM PROJECT_FOLDER START WITH PARENT_ID IS NULL CONNECT BY PRIOR FOLDER_ID = PARENT_ID ) WHERE PATH LIKE ?&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the &apos;&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;&apos; will be transformed to &apos;&apos; and causes SQLException when send to the db server.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
